org.cip4.elk.alces.swingui.tree.test
Class TestSessionNode

java.lang.Object
  javax.swing.tree.DefaultMutableTreeNode
      org.cip4.elk.alces.swingui.tree.test.TestSessionNode
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.tree.MutableTreeNode, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode, TestSession
public class TestSessionNode
extends javax.swing.tree.DefaultMutableTreeNode
implements TestSession

A DefaultMutableTreeNode implementation of a TestSession. This class wraps a non-Swing TestSession implementation. The wrapped TestSession contains the logic, this class is simply a wrapper allowing the TestSession to be displayed in a Swing JTree.

Author:
Claes Buckwalter

TestSessionNode

public TestSessionNode(TestSession testSession,
                       javax.swing.tree.DefaultTreeModel treeModel)
Creates an TestSession that is a TreeNode and wraps a non-Swing TestSession implementation. The wrapped TestSession contains the logic, this class is simply a wrapper allowing the TestSession to be displayed in a JTree.

Parameters:
testSession - The TestSession to wrap. This object may not be an instance of TreeNode.
treeModel - the tree model this node belongs to

TestSessionNode

public TestSessionNode(TestSession testSession,
                       javax.swing.tree.DefaultTreeModel treeModel,
                       boolean asyncMode)
Creates an TestSession that is a TreeNode and wraps a non-Swing TestSession implementation. The wrapped TestSession contains the logic, this class is simply a wrapper allowing the TestSession to be displayed in a JTree.

Parameters:
testSession - The TestSession to wrap. This object may not be an instance of TreeNode.
treeModel - the tree model this node belongs to
asyncMode - if true messages are queued and sent asynchronously; if false messages are sent synchronously
